        "step": 11,
        "type": "text",
        "text": "All 3 resistors are placed! Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Added 3 × 220Ω Current-Limiting Resistors\n\n| Resistor | Protects | Placed At |\n|----------|----------|-----------|\n| **R1 – 220Ω** | Red LED (x:0, y:9) | Row 11, Col 0 |\n| **R2 – 220Ω** | Green LED (x:4, y:9) | Row 11, Col 4 |\n| **R3 – 220Ω** | Red LED 2 (x:7, y:14) | Row 16, Col 7 |\n\n### Why 220Ω?\nWith a **5V** Arduino output and a typical LED forward voltage of ~2V:\n> **(5V − 2V) / 220Ω ≈ 13.6 mA** — safely within the ~20mA max rating of standard LEDs. 🟢\n\nEach resistor should be wired **in series** between the LED's cathode and GND to complete the protection circuit. Let me know if you'd like me to wire them up too!"
